ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a great course to take for a comprehensive look into American politics.

A good introduction to mainstream American politics. If you don't need an introduction, you'd better off going to Mayhew's office hours (he's quite generous with his time) and skipping the class entirely.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course was valuable in laying a strong foundation on issues pertaining to American politics.
Forced me to read basic American texts that will be on the American exam. Gave me the time to think about some particular issues that I'd like to pursue further in my own research.
